@startuml runtime-learning
title Runtime View — Learning Flywheel

actor Developer
participant "Claude Code" as CC
participant "/learn-eval\ncommand" as LE
participant "instinct store\n(~/.clarc/instincts/)" as IS
participant "/evolve\ncommand" as EV
participant "skills/\n(promoted skills)" as Skills
participant "agent-instincts/\n(session overlays)" as AI

== Observation ==
Developer -> CC: Session completes
CC -> LE: Developer invokes /learn-eval
LE -> LE: Quality gate:\n- Minimum confidence 0.7\n- Deduplication check\n- Save-location decision\n  (global vs project-scoped)
LE -> IS: Write instinct files\n(JSON with domain, pattern, confidence)

== Conflict Detection ==
IS -> IS: Scan for contradicting instincts\nin same domain
IS -> IS: Write conflicts.json

Developer -> CC: /instinct-status
CC -> IS: Read all instincts + conflicts
IS -> CC: Report by domain + confidence

== Evolution ==
Developer -> CC: /evolve (or auto Monday)
CC -> EV: Cluster accumulated instincts
EV -> EV: Identify stable high-signal patterns\n(confidence > 0.8, seen 3+ times)
EV -> Skills: Promote to permanent skill\n(skills/<domain>/SKILL.md update)
EV -> AI: Update agent-instinct overlays\n(injected at next SessionStart)

== Decay ==
IS -> IS: instinct-decay.js\n(reduce confidence of stale instincts\nif not reinforced for 30+ days)

@enduml
